    "title": "Mid-Level Fleet Manager at SpiceJet Cargo",
    "description": "Join the SpiceJet Cargo family as a Fleet Manager in Kochi. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout SpiceJet Cargo:\nSpiceJet Cargo is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage a fleet of vehicles and coordinate with drivers\n• Ensure compliance with transportation regulations and safety standards\n• Optimize delivery routes to reduce cost and improve efficiency\n• Coordinate with warehousing teams for inbound and outbound operations\n• Prepare MIS reports on delivery performance and SLA adherence\n• Manage relationships with third-party logistics providers\n• Conduct periodic vendor audits and evaluate logistics partners\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in TMS\n• Proficiency in SAP SCM\n• Proficiency in INCOTERMS\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in GPS Tracking Systems\n• Proficiency in Cold Chain Logistics\n• Proficiency in KPI Monitoring\n• Proficiency in Last Mile Delivery\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Referral bonus program\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Kochi, Kerala, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with SpiceJet Cargo!",
